						<p><hi rend="bold">Local chief Mīnāṭsi nāyakkar, Pārttiva = c. 17th-18th century. A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>One Mīnāṭchi-nāyakkar gave endowment of land for performing worship on all the 360 days of the year in the Pasupatīśvara temple at Kerpāpuri (i.e. Karur).</p>						

